{"title":"IMOS - ANMN National Reference Stations - Maria and North Stradbroke Islands - Near real-time wave height","recordAbstract":"This collection contains measurements of significant wave height transmitted in near real-time (no QC) from the National Reference Stations at Maria Island off the east coast of Tasmania (NRSMAI), and North Stradbroke Island in south-east Queensland (NRSNSI). In 2015 data was also provided from a mooring in the Palm Passage (2015-05-15 to 2016-11-27).

The National Reference Station network is designed to provide baseline information, at timescales relevant to human response, that is required to understand how large-scale, long-term change and variability in the global ocean are affecting the ecosystems of Australia's coastal seas. The stations are operated by the Australian National Moorings Network (ANMN), a facility of the Integrated Marine Observing System (IMOS).

This collection has been discontinued, as the real-time telemetry has been removed from the platforms."}

